                   -= Solamnian Knight Feelings =-

        Command         Description                          Type
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
        kaccept(T)      accept an offer (from someone)      BQCSR
        kadmire(T)      admire a Knight                     -Q---
        kamused         NOT amused                          BQCSR
        kaspire         attend to Squire duties             -Q---
        kassist(t)      offer assistance (to someone)       BQCSR
        kbow(t)         knightly bow (to someone)           --CSR
        kbrook(t)       brook no argument (from someone)    BQCSR
        kbye(t)         a formal farewell (to someone)      BQCSR
        kc1(t)          a combatcry (to someone)            BQCSR
        kc2(s)          a battlecry                         BQCSR
        kchant          Solamnian Death Chant               BQCSR
        kchaste(T)      give someone a chaste kiss          BQCSR
        kclasp(T)       clasp someone's hand in greeting    BQCSR
        kcount          count to ten to calm yourself       BQCSR
        kcrown          think of the Order of the Crown     -Q---
        kd1(T)          challenge someone to a duel         BQCSR
        kd2(T)          another challenge for a duel        BQCSR
        kdanger         look for signs of danger            BQCSR
        kdeclare        declare the Oath                    BQCSR
        kdeem(T)        deem someone a worthy fighter       BQCSR
        kdie            prepare for death                   BQCSR
        kfaith          express faith in the Knighthood     --C--
        kfirm           stand your ground                   BQCSR
        khand(T)        kiss someone's hand                 BQCSR
        khonour(T)      show someone the proper respect     -QCSR
        klaugh(t)       hearty laughter                     BQCSR
        klead(t)        offer to lead (someone)             ----R
        kmagic(t)       scorn magic (or a magic user)       BQCSR
        knees(T)        ask for someone's blessing          BQCSR
        knod(t)         indicate it's time to move on       BQCSR
        knose(t)        wrinkle nose in distaste            BCSR
        nsmile          smile like Nick                     BQCSR
        kobey(T)        nod in obedience to a Knight        -Q---
        pledge          pledge your blade to Paladine       BQCSR
        kpraise(S)      praise something                    BQCSR
        kpray(patron)   pray (to your patron)               BQCSR
        ks(S)           speak in Solamnian                  BQCSR
        ksage(t)        nod your head sagely                ----R
        salute(t)       salute (someone)                    BQCSR
 <kwep> ksalute2(t)     salute (someone) with your weapon   BQCSR
        kshake          frown at the unjust battle          ---S-
        ksing           sing a song of war                  BQCSR
        kslap(T)        slap someone (with a gauntlet)      BQCSR
        ksmooth(m,h)    smooth (m)oustache or (h)air        BQCSR
        ksomber         recall fallen comrades              BQCSR
        kstand(T)       stand at someone's side             --C--
        kstudy(t)       study your surroundings or someone  BQCSR
        kswear          your word as a Knight/Sentry        -QCSR
        ksweat          wipe the sweat from your brow       BQCSR
        kswift(T)       steal a swift kiss from someone     BQCSR
        kwar            prepare yourself for war            ---S-
        tend(S)         attend to your weapons or armour    BQCSR
        ktoast          toast to good fortune in battle     BQCSR
        ktrace          trace a scar absentmindedly         BQCSR
-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
Most emotes can be used with a four letter abbreviation - kamu (kamused)
Strings: T - requires target                 Types: B = Black Rose
         t - can be directed at a target            Q = Squire  R = Rose
         S - requires string                        C = Crown   S = Sword
